quran[22]{c,v,t}:
  76,1,"There was — was there not? — a time when man [before he was created] was not yet a thing worth mentioning"
  76,2,"It is, indeed, We who have created man out of a mixed [fertilized] ovum, so that We try him out. And then We made him a being endowed with hearing and sight"
  76,3,"We do indeed guide him, whether he be grateful or ungrateful"
  76,4,"For those who suppress the Truth, We have readied chains, and shackles, and a blazing Fire"
  76,5,The righteous indeed shall drink from a cup containing a camphor-flavoured beverage
  76,6,"A fountain from which Allah's subjects shall drink, making it flow as and when required"
  76,7,"They fulfill their vows, and fear a Day the evil of which would be widespread"
  76,8,"And they feed — for the sheer love of Him — the needy, the orphan, and the victim of circustances"
  76,9,"We feed you only for Allah's sake: we desire no recompense from you, nor thanks"
  76,10,"We do indeed fear from our Lord a distressful, disastrous Day"
  76,11,"And then, Allah will save them from the woes of that Day, and will bestow on them brightness and joy"
  76,12,"And He will reward them, for their patience, with Garden [Paradise] and silk [garments]"
  76,13,They will be reclining on couches there. They will feel neither sunburn therein nor intense cold
  76,14,"And its shadows will come down low over them, and its clusters of fruit will dangle within reach"
  76,15,And silver vessels and glass goblets will be passed around them
  76,16,"From silver [vessel] to glass [goblet] — [the drink will be poured out] in required quantity"
  76,17,"And in it [Paradise] they will be given to drink of a cup containing a ginger-flavoured beverage"
  76,18,"[The source of the beverage is a fountain] therein named `Salsabeel"
  76,19,And waiting upon them will be immortal boys. When you see them you would think they were pearls dispersed
  76,20,"And when you look, you would be looking at bliss and a realm transcendent"
  76,21,Upon them will be garments of green silk and brocade; and they will be adorned with silver bracelets. And their Lord will give them a pure drink
  76,22,"This indeed is a reward for you, and your struggle [in worldly life] is appreciated"